  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Tornado Recovery in Arkansas</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Family members,Individuals,Men</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Providing underserved Arkansas tornado survivors with long-term unmet needs from the April 27, 2015 tornadoes in Faulkner and Pulaski Counties.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Review requests for assistance received from individuals and/or from referral resource partners. Team members will actively seek those in need of continued assistance using a network of connections. ,Will continue in participation as a member organization with ARVOAD as one potential resource for referrals but will maintain control over Diocesan funds for assistance, in accordance with Diocesan guidelines developed for the use of these funds, and will reserve the flexibility to assist in cases refused for assistance by other organizations. ,Collaborate with the community and resource partners to fill the gaps in services for these underserved, providing such advocacy as is possible where appropriate,Provide emotional and spiritual care resources for the underserved after identifying those in need of such care.,Advocate for disaster preparation in the diocese when opportunities present.,Confirm that the request is for the underserved community (children, the elderly, low wage earners, undocumented and/or non-English speaking populations).,Assist those that are not approved for help by making referrals to other potential resources.,Maintain financial and statistical data on those served and on continuing unmet needs.,Provide financial assistance through the Episcopal Diocese of Arkansas, to cover unmet needs related to the tornado.</narrative>
  </description>
